Messages.Value: Thank you for calling XYZ Travel Agency, my name is Lily. How may I assist you today?
Hi Lily, my name is John Smith. I recently took a trip from Los Angeles to New York and I have a complaint about my experience.
I'm sorry to hear that, John. Can you please tell me a little bit more about what happened?
Yes, on my flight from Los Angeles to New York, my luggage was lost and I still haven't been able to locate it. I wanted to know if there is anything your agency can do to help me track it down.
I'm so sorry to hear that, John. I'll do everything I can to assist you. Can you please provide me with your flight details and your hotel reservation number?

Sure, my flight was with American Airlines and the flight number was AA123. The departure date was April 28th at 2:30pm. My hotel reservation was at the Hilton Hotel in New York and the reservation number is 456789. My check-in date was also April 28th.
Thank you for the information, John. I'll contact American Airlines and the Hilton Hotel to try to locate your luggage. I'll keep you updated every step of the way.
Thank you, Lily. I appreciate your help.
You're welcome, John. Is there anything else I can assist you with?
No, that's it. Thank you again, Lily.
You're welcome, John. Have a great day!
